# Cloudflare Pages header rules.
#
# This site has no build/bundling step — index.html etc. reference
# src/*.jsx and src/*.js directly by plain filename (no content hash), so
# there is nothing in the URL that changes when the file's content changes.
# Without this, Cloudflare's edge cache and browsers can keep serving a
# stale copy of a script for a long time after a new deploy, which has
# repeatedly shown up as "I pushed a fix but the site still behaves like
# the old code." Force revalidation on every request for anything that
# isn't a fingerprinted third-party asset, so a hard refresh (or even a
# normal reload) always gets the latest deployed version.

/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600
